Former IPID head, Robert McBride, says he believes former acting police commissioner, Khomotso Phahlane, chose a team to investigate corruption allegations against him in 2016. He was giving testimony before the commission of inquiry into state capture. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Ipid head Robert McBride says he believes former acting police commissioner Khomotso Phahlane chose a team to investigate corruption allegations against him in 2016. He was giving testimony before the commission of inquiry into state capture. WATCH: State capture inquiry hears testimony on law enforcement He also says he believes former Hawks head in the North West Jan Mabula should have recused himself from the investigation. The former Ipid head is now the new Director of the foreign branch of the State Security Agency. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his approval of this appointment, which is for a 3-year term from 1 July 2020 to 30 June 2023.